HEADWORD: Polymer
<hw>Pol"y*mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Polymeric</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of two or
more substances related to each other by polymerism; specifically, a
substance produced from another substance by chemical
polymerization.</def> <mark>[Formerly also written polymere.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

